faqs.question: What forms of payment are accepted?
faqs.answer: You can register Visa, MasterCard, American Express and Discover cards in the app. Payment cards registered must be issued by a U.S. bank. If you have an iOS device, and your card is registered to your Apple Wallet, Apple Pay will automatically function as a payment option within the McDonald’s app. If you have registered a card to the Google Pay™ app on your Android, you can select Google Pay™ as a payment method in the [McDonald's app](https://www.mcdonalds.com/us/en-us/download-app.html). Payments with PayPal and Venmo are now also available with Mobile Order & Pay.

faqs.question: Does McDonald’s have Contactless Delivery?
faqs.answer: Contactless delivery is available through our partners as no-contact delivery on DoorDash, no-contact delivery on Uber Eats, contact-free on Grubhub, and non-contact delivery on Postmates.

faqs.question: How Does McDonald’s Curbside Pickup Work?
faqs.answer: By using the [McDonald’s app](https://www.mcdonalds.com/us/en-us/download-app.html) you can get your food via curbside without leaving your vehicle.

faqs.question: How Do I Order McDonald’s Contactless Delivery?
faqs.answer: To order McDonald’s contactless delivery, select your favorites in DoorDash, Uber Eats, Grubhub, or Postmates as you usually would. When you are checking out, choose the “Leave at Door” option in the Uber Eats app, “Leave at my door” option in the DoorDash app, or "contact-free delivery" in the Grubhub app, or choose the dropoff option "Leave order at my door" on Postmates.

faqs.question: Is There Recording Happening at McDonald’s Restaurants?
faqs.answer: Yes, we record video for service improvement, technology development and security purposes. Find more information in the[recording notice FAQ](https://www.mcdonalds.com/us/en-us/faq/mcdonalds-app.html#recording-notice).

faqs.question: What is a Star?
faqs.answer: Stars are the loyalty currency you earn as a member of Starbucks® Rewards that can be redeemed for choices of Rewards such as free or discounted items at Starbucks. Stars can only be redeemed through the Starbucks® Indonesia mobile app.

faqs.question: What are the benefits for Green Members?
faqs.answer: Green members in Starbucks Rewards™ can convert collected Stars into various Reward options: 30 Stars for a Free Selected Add-On (Espresso Shot/Syrup/Sauce), 60 Stars for a Free Tall sized Americano or Brewed Tea, or 120 Stars for any Free Tall sized Handcrafted Beverage or any Food. Green members also receive Birthday Treats on their birthday, including 25 Bonus Stars, a Birthday Cake Reward, and 2x Stars on their transaction.

faqs.question: How to redeem a Reward in-App?
faqs.answer: To redeem a Reward in-App, first you must log-in to your Starbucks account, choose the "Redeem ☆" button, then select your Reward option by clicking "use xx ☆" until a redemption success prompt appears. Your new Reward will then be added under the "Reward details" tab. If you don’t see your recently converted Rewards, please refresh the "Reward details" tab or page.

faqs.question: What is a Starbucks Card?
faqs.answer: A Starbucks Card is a stored value card that you can use as a payment method at any Starbucks in Indonesia. You must activate and register your Starbucks Card to join the Starbucks Rewards™ program and gain access to its features and benefits.

faqs.question: How do I register my card?
faqs.answer: To register your card, download the Starbucks® Indonesia mobile app or visit cms.starbucks.co.id/card to create an account. You will need your physical card with you and follow the instructions to register your card.
